  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: necessary-sufficient confusion)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE (adversarial insertion): The decision rationale treats the presence of the relative-hemolysis-index (RH) threshold alarm — a necessary screening condition — as a sufficient basis for accepting the model for the broader COU safety goal, without formally addressing model-form adequacy, input uncertainty propagation, or equivalency of in-vitro test conditions to clinical use.",
